programExec.step4:
NODE SUMMARY — two-part output (runs AFTER each node in step3): (A) OUTPUT: Read {AIAP_NAME}.{NodeName}.json cache file. Extract output field (Sub Agent's original findings). Forward verbatim to user — this is the Sub Agent's raw output. (B) EXPLAIN (B1 v5.13.0 — FORCED USER LANGUAGE): Orchestrator writes its own detailed explanation for the user. Read user_summary + output + tool_calls + modifications from cache. USER LANGUAGE DETECTION (Q2 v5.13.0 — explicit fallback priority chain): detect user's language using the following priority: (1) conversation_context — scan recent user_message turns for dominant language (Chinese, English, etc.); (2) if conversation_context unavailable or language ambiguous, fall back to output_mode default language; (3) if output_mode does not specify a language, fall back to the orchestrator's current conversation language (A2 v5.14.1 BUG FIX: detect from the latest user_message in conversation_context or _index.json::user_message; if still undetectable, use English as ultimate fallback). EXPLAIN narrative MUST be rendered in the detected user language — the user reads the EXPLAIN section to understand what happened. Structure tokens are preserved in their original form (NodeName identifiers, status enum values like PASS/FAIL, file paths, version numbers, technical identifiers) — only the narrative explanation text is translated. Example: 'Node Summary: [6/21] Generate1 (agent) PASS
[Chinese narrative explaining what Generate1 did, what files were modified, what scores were achieved...]'. Include specific numbers, file names, findings. No length limit — write as much as needed for the user to understand. The user sees BOTH: (1) Sub Agent's output (verbatim, original language) and (2) Orchestrator's explain (forced user language). Format: 'Node Summary: [{N}/{total}] {NodeName} ({mode}) {status}
{orchestrator explain — detailed narrative in user language}'. The prefix 'Node Summary:' is MANDATORY. You MUST output this BEFORE proceeding to the next node. USER MESSAGE: After Node Summary, check Sub Agent return result for user_messages content. If Sub Agent reported any user_messages (non-empty), output each one using the exact prefix '**User Message:** {content}'. This is MANDATORY — these are messages the Sub Agent generated for the user during execution. Node Summary first, then User Message. Repeat step3->step4 for each node.
